      "file_path": "onboarding/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 124,
      "message": "1. The line indentation is broken - it is difficult to read.\n2. We try our best to avoid new profiles, definitely not for just a simple flag (\"-P onboarding\" vs \"-Djacoco.skip=false\").\n3. This profile clashes with the one defined in the root pom (sdc/pom.xml), so that running the usual \"mvn clean install -P onboarding\" behaves differently, because jacoco.skip is \"true\" there, which it must be by default.",
